																				<article class="col insidepagethumbholder nocategory ">
								<a href="https://hakaimagazine.com/news/foraging-food-forging-bonds/" class="tagmanager" id="Related_article_34233" >
								<img width="900" height="432" src="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-woman-gleaners.jpg" class="insidepagethumb wp-post-image" alt="Women forage for marine animals on the rocky shore near Adara, a village on Atauro Island, Timor-Leste" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-woman-gleaners.jpg 2500w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-woman-gleaners-520x250.jpg 520w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-woman-gleaners-768x369.jpg 768w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-woman-gleaners-1200x576.jpg 1200w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-woman-gleaners-1536x738.jpg 1536w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-woman-gleaners-2048x984.jpg 2048w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-woman-gleaners-900x432.jpg 900w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px" />								<header class="insidepagethumbinfo">
									<h2>Foraging Food, Forging Bonds</h2>
									<h3>From socializing outdoors to relishing a favorite snack, the women of Timor-Leste glean for myriad reasons—and they go beyond food security.</h3>
									<p class="insidepagethumbinfodate">Mar 8, 2021 | 650 words, about 3 minutes</p>
